<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900816-0108</DOCNO><DOCID>900816-0108.</DOCID><HL>   Technology:   On-Line Software International</HL><DATE>08/16/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   OSI</CO><LP>   FORT LEE, N.J. -- On-Line Software International Inc.'sboard approved a measure designed to make hostile takeoversprohibitively expensive.   The computer software and services company will distributerights to buy preferred stock to holders of common shares onSept. 6. Under certain circumstances, the rights allow theholders to buy shares of On-Line or its buyer at half price.</LP><TEXT>   A spokeswoman said the board, which announced the actionTuesday, knows of no attempts to take control of On-LineSoftware.   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,On-Line shares closed at $7 a share, up 25 cents.</TEXT></DOC>